# NestJS API Conventions

## Module Structure

- One module per feature domain: `auth/`, `chat/`, `agent/`, `provider/`, `admin/`, `audit/`.
- Each module has: `*.module.ts`, `*.service.ts`, `*.controller.ts`.
- Barrel export from each module's `index.ts`.

## Controllers

- Controllers handle HTTP only — no business logic. Validate → delegate to service → respond.
- Use `@ApiTags()`, `@ApiOperation()`, `@ApiResponse()` on every method (Swagger).
- Apply `@UseGuards(JwtAuthGuard, RolesGuard)` at controller level.
- Use `@Roles('admin')` or `@Roles('admin', 'developer')` on routes that need RBAC.

```typescript
// ✅ Thin controller with Zod validation + RBAC
@Post()
@Roles('admin', 'developer')
@UsePipes(new ZodValidationPipe(createAgentSchema))
@ApiOperation({ summary: 'Create agent' })
async create(@Body() dto: CreateAgentDto, @CurrentUser() user: User) {
  return this.agentService.create(user.id, dto);
}
```

## DTOs & Validation

- Zod schemas in `@centrai/types` are the single source of truth for validation.
- Use a `ZodValidationPipe` (custom or `nestjs-zod`) to validate request bodies against Zod schemas.
- Separate `CreateDto`, `UpdateDto`, and `ResponseDto` per entity — all derived from Zod with `z.infer<>`.
- Transform/strip unknown fields at the pipe level, not in services.

## Guards & RBAC

- `JwtAuthGuard` — verifies JWT token.
- `RolesGuard` — checks `user.role` against `@Roles()` metadata.
- Admin endpoints: `@Roles('admin')`. Agent CRUD: `@Roles('admin', 'developer')`. Chat: any authenticated user.
- End users hitting admin endpoints must receive 403, never 404.

## Provider Adapter Pattern

- All LLM providers implement `ProviderAdapter` interface: `complete()`, `listModels()`, `healthCheck()`.
- Normalize to OpenAI chat completion format internally.
- Streaming via `Observable<CompletionChunk>`.

## Error Handling

- Throw NestJS `HttpException` subclasses (`NotFoundException`, `ForbiddenException`, etc.).
- Global exception filter wraps all errors in `{ data: null, error: { code, message }, meta }` envelope.
- Log errors with NestJS `Logger` — include request ID for tracing.

## Agent Publish Workflow

- New agents start as `draft`. Only `published` agents appear in `GET /agents/published`.
- `POST /agents/:id/publish` transitions `draft → published`.
- Never expose `systemPrompt` to end-user-facing endpoints.
